12/05/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano on Wednesday (11 May) assured the OSCE Ambassador to Tirana, Pavel Vacek, and the head of the International Election-Monitoring Mission, Jorgen Grunnet, that the Albanian government is committed to implementation of the country's new electoral code, as well as co-operation with the international community in the election process. 
Nano vowed that the government would work to guarantee free and democratic parliamentary elections on 3 July.
In a meeting Wednesday with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn stressed the importance of the election process for Albania's EU integration bid. 
(Albanian government, Albanian Presidency Web site - 12/05/05)
